textAfterTable: 133528 Ceragioli           Discovered 2003 Oct. 4 by D. Healy at Junk Bond Observatory. Roger Ceragioli (b. 1959) is senior optician at the University of Arizona's Steward Mirror Laboratory. His projects include the "90-Prime" focus corrector for the Bok Telescope and the MODS spectrograph for the Large Binocular Telescope. His Ph.D. dissertation was on "The lore and poetry of the Dog Star in antiquity".
